title: For Sale:  Complete Glock Gen 3 Slide w/ Silencerco Threaded barrel, LPK, and OEM Mag
postcontent: Like new less than 10 rounds fired through it!Selling my complete Glock 17 Generation 3 Upper. It comes with an aftermarket Silencerco Threaded Barrel ready to accept a suppressor, muzzle brake, compensator, or whatever else you would like to thread onto it. The slide is complete with Ghost Ring sights that double as night sights. I actually really like these sight and am going to install some on my 1911. The package is complete with a lower parts kit, and 1 standard OEM Glock magazine. This is perfect for Polymer 80 builds since that was what these parts were on. I am also throwing in the Polymer 80 locking block/ rail mechanism with the screws to fix it to the polymer 80 frame; however, you will not need this if you buy a new Polymer 80 frame as it will come with a brand new one. You could also buy a stripped Glock 17 Generation 3 frame and put this build together that way. The barrel, sights, and channel liner were all installed by a gunsmith. I shot a total of 7 rounds with these parts attached before realizing that I do not like the way Glock type handguns feel in my hands. Everything functioned decently; since I shot such a small amount of rounds through it, you will still have to go through a break-in period for the handgun especially if you go down the polymer 80 route. I am selling everything for under what I paid for it excluding the installation fee I got from the gunsmith!! I am selling it because I know it will sit in my safe and never be touched so I do not mind letting go of it for less than what I put into even though everything is still practically brand new (there are some moderate wear marks here and there). I can ship anywhere (legally of course) with either FedEx or UPS and it will be completely free for you, or we can meet up anywhere in Atlanta or Augusta since I go there from time to time. Make sure these components are legal in your state if you want me to ship; I would hate having to cancel because of legality issues! Thanks for looking at my post and have a great day!!
